Goal: Show how PPI and CPI compare over long-term vs short-term trends. (Blue is the forecast and Green is the result.) 
Chart 2 highlights which categories experienced the biggest differences between long-term inflation and short-term changes. Eggs, cereals/bakery products, and sugar show significant spikes relative to their 20-year averages, while fresh fruits and vegetables fell below historical norms. This reveals where consumers are facing the most (or least) pressure. 
